{
  "name": "smooth_shift",
  "description": "Reference-parity golden fixtures for the Smooth Shift + Thicken interactive tool (mesh.smoothShiftTool, task 0358). Frozen from a live reference-editor capture: a stock unit cube (segments=1, 8v/6f), top face selected only (y>0.4), the tool's 5 attrs driven numerically, applied once. Every case here is a topology-CHANGING op (adds cap/skin verts+faces), so it uses the topology-diff verifier (count deltas + bidirectional position match) rather than the rigid-cluster before/after-pair verifier. 'base_noop', 'shift03', and 'thicken_top_only' are the 3 combos this task requires at minimum; 'shift03_scale05' and 'thicken_top_only_noshift' are additional frozen combos from the same capture session that pin the scale-about-centroid law and the thicken+shift=0 interaction respectively. No reference engine runs at test time — the geometry below is transcribed from the frozen capture and independently re-derived analytically (see the smoothShiftFacesByMask doc comment in source/mesh.d) before being pinned here.",
  "source": "Frozen reference-editor capture (task 0358 toolcard), numeric tool.attr + apply on a stock cube's top face.",
  "tolerance": 1e-4,
  "cases": [
    {
      "name": "base_noop",
      "input": [
        { "reset": true },
        { "select": { "mode": "polygons", "coords": [
          [[-0.5,0.5,-0.5],[0.5,0.5,-0.5],[0.5,0.5,0.5],[-0.5,0.5,0.5]]
        ] } }
      ],
      "expected_before": { "verts": 8, "faces": 6 },
      "op": [
        { "smooth_shift": { "shift": 0.0, "scale": 1.0, "thicken": false } }
      ],
      "expected_after": { "verts": 12, "faces": 10 },
      "expected_vertices": [
